{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XTrtmoCMsrJFnPPCVn5sAc","type":"tool_result","content":"  1920→- **The bug has been flagged in 8 consecutive retros and remains unfixed.** This is a process failure — retro action items are not being executed.\n  1921→- **Ralph does not know the sprint is done.** It keeps launching sessions, each of which re-triggers the reconciliation bug.\n  1922→- **Retros are being run for zero-work sessions.** This session's retro is itself waste — the right answer was to fix the bug, not write another retro about it.\n  1923→\n  1924→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  1925→\n  1926→1. **`done` must be treated as a terminal state.** The reconciliation code must never regress a story from `done` to any earlier status. Proof documents in git are the authoritative source — if a proof document exists and is committed, the story is done, period.\n  1927→\n  1928→2. **Ralph needs proof-document-aware reconciliation.** Instead of relying on heuristics about working directory state, reconciliation should check:\n  1929→   - Does `_bmad-output/proof/{story-id}*.md` exist in the git index?\n  1930→   - Was the story committed with a `done` status in any prior commit?\n  1931→   - If either is true, the story status is `done` and must not be changed.\n  1932→\n  1933→3. **Action items from retros must have owners and deadlines.** Flagging the same bug in 8 retros without fixing it means the retro process is broken. Action items need to be converted to actual stories or tasks with assigned execution time.\n  1934→\n  1935→4. **Zero-work sessions should not trigger full retros.** A one-line state marker (\"session 13: no work, state fix only\") would suffice and save the cost of a full retro cycle.\n  1936→\n  1937→5. **Ralph needs a sprint-complete termination condition.** When `sprint.done === sprint.totalStories`, ralph should emit a completion message and stop. No reconciliation, no new sessions, no further cost.\n  1938→\n  1939→## 7. Action Items\n  1940→\n  1941→| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n  1942→|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n  1943→| 1 | **Fix state reconciliation to treat `done` as terminal** — add guard: `if (current === 'done') return`. Never regress from `done`. | CRITICAL | Infrastructure | OPEN — **flagged 8 consecutive sessions (5-13), unfixed. This is the single highest-ROI fix in the project.** |\n  1944→| 2 | **Add ralph sprint-complete termination** — stop launching sessions when 100% done | CRITICAL | Infrastructure | OPEN — **flagged 5 consecutive sessions (9-13)** |\n  1945→| 3 | **Make reconciliation proof-document-aware** — check git index for proof docs before modifying story status | HIGH | Infrastructure | NEW |\n  1946→| 4 | **Skip full retros for zero-work sessions** — emit a one-line marker instead | MEDIUM | Process | OPEN (carried from session 12) |\n  1947→| 5 | **Convert retro action items to stories with deadlines** — retros without follow-through are waste | MEDIUM | Process | NEW |\n  1948→| 6 | **Reduce \"unknown\" story cost bucket** ($118.64 / 18.8% unattributed) | LOW | Tooling | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1949→| 7 | **Plan next sprint** — all 17 epics complete, need new work items | HIGH | PM | OPEN (carried forward) |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QqbYDeHqHaRTpYzpGo6XWM","session_id":"48915292-5899-47d6-b845-e95e04d3b9ff","uuid":"2be1f5f4-4b23-4595-ba40-50717daf229e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:33:29.502Z"}
